=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527873\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 16, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gjf1665702773980.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gjf1665702773980.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gjf1665702773980.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gjf1665702773980\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Navigate to specific ProcScript modules in components or global ProcScript using the\n      Debugger Browser, and use the browser to set breakpoints and watches. </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9230e1_d9231e1_d9232e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__p_d18962e1_d18963e1_d18964e1\">From the <span class=\"keyword wintitle\">Debugger</span> main\n               window, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Browser</span></span>. The browser window is displayed.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__note_N10038_N10035_N1001C_N10019_N10016_N10001\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> From the <span class=\"keyword wintitle\">Call Stack</span> window, you can open the\n                  browser at a specific module by double-clicking it.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9233e1_d9234e1_d9235e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Double-click the appropriate icon to expand its structure.  </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">If ProcScript code is available, the code is displayed in the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Trigger/Module</span> pane.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9236e1_d9237e1_d9238e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To open another structure, click the open icon in the browser's toolbar, and select\n               a structure.</span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9239e1_d9240e1_d9241e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose a structure of <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Type</span>. </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9242e1_d9243e1_d9244e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you chose <code class=\"ph codeph\">Global ProcScript</code> in the\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Type</span> field, choose the source from the\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Look in</span> field.</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9245e1_d9246e1_d9247e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__p_d18965e1_d18966e1_d18967e1\">Optionally specify a\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Subsytem</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure Name</span> or\n                     a <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Library</span>.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">You can enter a name, a retrieve profile, or leave it blank (the same as\n                     GOLD *).</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9248e1_d9249e1_d9250e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Retrieve</span> to retrieve all structures matching\n                     your retrieve profiles. Then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9251e1_d9252e1_d9253e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To toggle in a displayed ProcScript module, select the ProcScript line in the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Trigger/Module</span> pane and click the breakpoints icon in the\n               browser's toolbar.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9254e1_d9255e1_d9256e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To watch a field or variable, highlight the field or variable name in the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure</span> pane, right-click and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Add\n                  Watch</span>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9257e1_d9258e1_d9259e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To set or remove a break point, right-click the line of code and choose\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle Break Point</span>.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__li_d9260e1_d9261e1_d9262e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__p_d18968e1_d18969e1_d18970e1\">To edit the value of a field or variable,\n               double-click the field or variable name. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Alternatively, highlight the field or variable name in the Structure pane,\n               right-click, and choose a value.</div>\n<div class=\"itemgroup stepresult\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gjf1665702773980__p_d18971e1_d18972e1_d18973e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit Field, Variable, or\n                     Watch</span> form is displayed.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/crg1665703529113.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Open Structure</a><p>Select a structure (a component or global ProcScript) to be opened for the Debugger Browser window. The Open Structure form is accessible only via the open icon in the browser’s toolbar.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pxo1665702773911.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Monitoring ProcScript Modules</a><p>The Uniface Debugger allows you to monitor and control the execution of ProcScript.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xbe1665702773834.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call Stack</a><p>View the ProcScript call stack to see the modules that are called or activated at runtime, or to identify where to put a try-catch block to handle exceptions.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527873\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527873\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Browsing ProcScript Modules in the Uniface Debugger Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 16, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Navigate to specific ProcScript modules in components or global ProcScript using the Debugger Browser, and use the browser to set breakpoints and watches. From the Debugger main window, choose View > Browser . The browser window is displayed. Tip: From the Call Stack window, you can open the browser at a specific module by double-clicking it. Double-click the appropriate icon to expand its structure. If ProcScript code is available, the code is displayed in the Trigger/Module pane. To open another structure, click the open icon in the browser's toolbar, and select a structure. Choose a structure of Type . If you chose Global ProcScript in the Type field, choose the source from the Look in field. Optionally specify a Subsytem and Structure Name or a Library . You can enter a name, a retrieve profile, or leave it blank (the same as GOLD *). Click Retrieve to retrieve all structures matching your retrieve profiles. Then click Open . To toggle in a displayed ProcScript module, select the ProcScript line in the Trigger/Module pane and click the breakpoints icon in the browser's toolbar. To watch a field or variable, highlight the field or variable name in the Structure pane, right-click and choose Add Watch . To set or remove a break point, right-click the line of code and choose Toggle Break Point . To edit the value of a field or variable, double-click the field or variable name. Alternatively, highlight the field or variable name in the Structure pane, right-click, and choose a value. The Edit Field, Variable, or Watch form is displayed. Related Links Open Structure Select a structure (a component or global ProcScript) to be opened for the Debugger Browser window. The Open Structure form is accessible only via the open icon in the browser’s toolbar. Monitoring ProcScript Modules The Uniface Debugger allows you to monitor and control the execution of ProcScript. Call Stack View the ProcScript call stack to see the modules that are called or activated at runtime, or to identify where to put a try-catch block to handle exceptions. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}